messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full path:
- /api/profiles/{username}

HTTP methods:
- all methods accepted (override): false
- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- In hello.go the profiles router group is mounted under the API prefix:
  - v1 := r.Group("/api")
  - users.ProfileRegister(v1.Group("/profiles"))
  => this composes to the prefix /api + /profiles.
- In users/routers.go ProfileRegister registers ProfileRetrieve only for GET on the path "/:username":
  - router.GET("/:username", ProfileRetrieve)
  => this yields the endpoint /api/profiles/:username, represented here as /api/profiles/{username}.
- There is no router.Any, no wildcard/“all methods” registration, so "all methods" is false.
- Only GET is explicitly registered for the exact path /api/profiles/{username}, so GET = true.
- HEAD, POST, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, DELETE, PATCH are not registered for the exact path /api/profiles/{username}; therefore they are false. (Note: POST and DELETE are registered in users/routers.go but for the different path "/:username/follow" — not for "/:username" itself.)
